# Styling & theming (Tailwind v4 + shadcn tokens)

## How theming works here
- Tailwind v4, **CSS-first**. `src/app/globals.css` imports `tailwindcss`, `tw-animate-css`, and
  `shadcn/tailwind.css`, then defines the theme as **CSS variables in `oklch`** under `:root`
  and `.dark`. There is **no `tailwind.config.js`** — do not create one.
- Colors are exposed as semantic tokens through the `@theme inline` block. Radius scales from
  `--radius`; headings use `font-heading`.

## Use semantic tokens, never hardcoded colors
Style with token utilities so light/dark and re-theming work automatically:
`bg-background` / `text-foreground`, `bg-card` / `text-card-foreground`, `bg-primary` /
`text-primary-foreground`, `text-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `bg-muted` / `text-muted-foreground`,
`bg-accent` / `text-accent-foreground`, `text-destructive` / `bg-destructive`, `border` (border-border),
`ring-ring`. **Do not** write `sky-600`, `slate-900`, `emerald-100`, etc.

## Re-theming for a new client (the money move)
- To rebrand (law-firm navy, restaurant warm orange, …) edit `--primary`, `--ring`, and optionally
  `--accent` in **both** `:root` and `.dark` in `globals.css`. Every `Button`, `Badge`, link, and
  token-styled element updates at once. Never hardcode a brand color inside a component.

## Dark mode
- Driven by `next-themes` with `attribute="class"` (the `.dark` class). The `ThemeProvider` wraps
  the app in `layout.tsx`, which also sets `suppressHydrationWarning` on `<html>` — keep both.
- Because you style with tokens, components are dark-ready by default. Add `dark:` utilities only
  for genuine special cases, not for base colors.

## Layout patterns (reuse)
- Page container: `mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6`; sections `py-16`.
- Mobile-first: base styles for small screens, add `sm:` / `md:` / `lg:` upward.
- Prefer composing shadcn `Card` over hand-built bordered boxes; size icons with `size-*`.
